7. What is directive? Types of directives in Angular? =>
  Angular directives are of three types:
   1.Component Directive => A component is actually a special type of directive with a template.
   2.Structural Directives => change the structure of the DOM by adding or removing elements.(ex: *ngIf, *ngFor,*ngSwitch, ngTemplate)
   3.Attribute Directives => change the appearance or behavior of an existing element.(ngClass, ngStyle)
   4.last Custom directive 

  What is a Custom Structural Directive? => changes the DOM structure by adding or removing elements.
